.\" Manpage for wxhearts
.TH WXHEARTS 6 "2026-04-19" "wxhearts 1.0" "Games Manual"
.SH NAME
wxhearts \- the classic Hearts card game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxhearts
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wxhearts
is a graphical implementation of the classic trick-taking card game Hearts
for four players. You play against three computer opponents. The game is
played with a standard 52-card deck; cards are ranked from 2 (lowest) to
Ace (highest) in each of the four suits.
.SH OBJECT
The object of Hearts is to have the lowest score at the end of the game.
.SH PLAY
.IP 1. 4
Choose three cards to pass to an opponent (except for every fourth hand,
when no cards are passed). To select a card to pass, click it. To cancel
the selection of a card, click it again.
.IP 2. 4
The player who has the two of clubs starts the play by leading with it.
.IP 3. 4
Each player, moving clockwise, clicks a card to play. You must play a card
in the same suit. If you do not have one, you can play any card, except
that you cannot play a heart or the queen of spades on the first trick.
.PP
The person who plays the highest card of the same suit as the first card
played takes the trick. That player starts the next trick by clicking a
card to lead. You cannot lead with a heart until a heart has been played
on a previous trick.
.SH SCORING
.IP \(bu 4
At the end of each hand, you get one point for each heart in your hand
and 13 points for the queen of spades. The game continues until one
player gets 100 points or more, or until the dealer quits the game.
.IP \(bu 4
If you win all the hearts and the queen of spades in one hand (called
.BR "Shooting the Moon" ),
then you score zero points and each other player scores 26 points.
.SH STRATEGY
.IP \(bu 4
Avoid taking a trick containing hearts or the queen of spades. The only
time you will want to take such tricks is when you are trying to Shoot
the Moon or trying to prevent someone else from successfully Shooting
the Moon.
.IP
To
.I "Shoot the Moon"
is to collect all the hearts and the queen of spades. When that happens,
you score zero points and each other player scores 26 points. Your
chances of successfully Shooting the Moon are best if your hand contains
a large number of high-value hearts and spades.
.IP \(bu 4
On hands that begin by passing cards to an opponent, pass cards with
high values, such as aces or face cards.
.IP \(bu 4
Play your highest cards early in the game, while your opponents are
likely to have some cards in each suit and will have to play those
cards instead of hearts. Tricks that do not contain any hearts or the
queen of spades do not add to your score.
.IP \(bu 4
Keep track of which cards have been played, particularly whether the
queen of spades has been played and whether hearts have been broken
(that is, whether a heart has been discarded on an earlier trick).
